&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a motivated and enthusiastic individual to join the Data Quality Department in a Team Lead Role, supporting the demands generated by the Trust Information Systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust recognises the importance of reliable information as a fundamental requirement for the speedy and effective treatment of patients. Data Quality is crutial and the availability of complete, accurate and timely data is important in supporting patient care, clinical governance, managment requirementsa dn service agreemens for healthcare planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will support the Data Quality Team to ensure that complete, accurate and timely data is recorded on the Trusts computerised systems to the highest data quality standard. In addition, the postholder will take a leading role in the training, validation and recording of the 18 week pathways following Department of Health guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will also assist in the development of data quality within the Trust as it affects the collection of patient data on the Patient Administration Dystem and other relevant Trust systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name   Helen Hocking&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title   Data Quality Manager&lt;/p&gt;
